Subject: Marine Battery Box

> If you live in a wet climate, you may want to
> consider putting your 
> battery in a marine-style battery box to keep
> it clean. Keeping your 
> battery and electrical connections clean is a
> helpful part of regular 
> bus maintenance.

It seems to me that this would always be a good
idea, even for people who don't live in rainy
areas.  Corrosion underneath the battery is a
major problem in all acvw's, which would also be
prevented by the marine battery box.   
